18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2401,
19 is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 2401. Sections 4 2401 through 10 2407 of this
21 act title shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
22 State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Act.".
23 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2402,
24 is amended to read as follows:
HB1282 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 Section 2402. A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma
2 State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program. The
3 purpose of the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising
4 Scholars Award Program is to retain top-ranked students from
5 Oklahoma in Oklahoma colleges, enable Oklahoma institutions
6 of higher education to compete aggressively for top Oklahoma
7 scholars, attract high-caliber out-of-state students to
8 Oklahoma to attend colleges and universities, and enhance the
9 academic quality in Oklahoma colleges and universities. The
10 program shall provide participants funding for enrollment
11 fees, tuition and other fees, room and board and required
12 textbooks or materials for up to five (5) years of
13 undergraduate and/or graduate study at accredited
14 institutions of higher education in Oklahoma.
15 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
16 administer the provisions of the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic
17 Rising Scholars Award Program.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2403, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 2403. A. No person shall be eligible to participate in
21 the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program
22 unless the person:
23 1. Has complied with all of the rules promulgated by the
24 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education pursuant to the
HB1282 HFLR Page 2
