1 prov isions of the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars
2 Award Act, Section 2401 et seq. of this title, for the award,
3 regulation, and administration of scholarships; and
4 2. Qualifies as one of the following:
5 a. an Individual Applicant Qualified Student, which shall
6 mean a student who is a resident of the State of
7 Oklahoma whose American College Testing Program score
8 or whose Scholastic Aptitude Test score falls within
9 the 99.5 to 100.0 percentile levels as administered in
10 the State of Oklahoma and whose grade point average
11 and/or class rank is exceptional, as determined by the
12 State Regents,
13 b. a Presidential Scholar, which shall mean a student
14 selected by the Commission on Presidential Scholars
15 administered by the United States Department of
16 Education,
