8 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2404, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 Section 2404. A. Scholarships awarded under the Oklahoma State
11 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program shall be awarded to
12 all eligible applicants without any limitation on the number of
13 scholarships to be awarded in any year other than the amount of
14 funds available for the scholarship program and the number of
15 eligible applicants.
16 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may, at the
17 time a scholarship is awarded to a student, set aside in the
18 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Trust Fund
19 funds for the full five-year commitment made to such eligible
20 scholar. For all academic years, students who have previously
21 received academic scholarships under the provisions of this act and
22 who have continued at all times to fulfill the requirements for
23 eligibility to receive academic scholarships provided in this act
24 shall be given an absolute priority for continued financial support
HB1282 HFLR Page 8
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 by t he Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award
2 Program superior to any students who are applying for such academic
3 scholarships awards for the first time.
4 C. In addition to the qualifications specified in Section 2403
5 of this title, the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may
6 adopt additional criteria for selection and allocation of awards
7 which may include, but are not limited to, consideration of high
8 school academic performance and personal interviews. The Oklahoma
9 State Regents for Higher Education shall annually report on the
10 number of former Academic Rising Scholars Award Program participants
11 who stay in state as compared to those who leave Oklahoma within
12 five (5) years of leaving the Award Program. In addition, the
13 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education are hereby authorized to
14 determine a maximum number of awards or a maximum amount of funding
15 which may go to nonresident students. Such maximum limitations
16 shall not exceed twenty-five percent (25%) of the awards or amount
17 of funding in any category provided in paragraph 2 of subsection A
18 of Section 2403 of this title.
19 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2405, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 2405. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
22 may adopt rules and regulations, prescribe and provide appropriate
23 forms for application, and employ such persons, contract for such
24 services and make such additional expenditures as may be necessary
HB1282 HFLR Page 9
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 or a ppropriate for implementing the provisions of the Oklahoma State
2 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Act; provided, as part of
3 the regulations adopted for administration of the provisions of the
4 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program, the
5 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall require that each
6 scholarship recipient make continuing and satisfactory progress
